@c -*- texinfo -*-

@chapter Vim Options

@float Figure,fig:screenshot_vim
@center @image{screenshots/bashstyle-ng_vim,,, BashStyle-NG Vim Settings, png}
@caption{Vim Settings}
@end float

@heading Basic

@defvr {Setting} use_vimcfg
This master switch will make @b{BashStyle-NG} adjust the Settings for @code{Vim}.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} vim_backup
If enabled @code{vim} will backup files to @code{filename~} upon @code{write}.
@end defvr

@heading Editing

@defvr {Setting} jump_back Jump back to last position
When opening a file again, @code{vim} will jump back to the previous position.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} filetype_indent Enable filetype indention
If enabled @code{vim} will use indention based on determined file type.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} show_command Display (partial) command
If enabled @code{vim} will display (partially) typed in commands in the ruler.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} highlight_brackets Highlight matching brackets
If enabled @code{vim} will highlight matching brackets, when the cursor is
positioned at either of them.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} syntax_hilight Enable syntax highlighting
Enable @code{vim} syntax highlighting.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} dark_background Bash has dark background
Determines whether the shell has dark background or not
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} start_line Jump to start of line
If enabled many jump commands move the cursor to the first non-blank character
of a line.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} wrap_line Wrap long lines
Wrap long lines exceeding @code{wrap_length}.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} wrap_length Autowrap position
At what length long lines should be wraped
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} tab_length tabstop length
Length of a tabulator in spaces.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} expandtab Expand tab to spaces
If enabled, tabulators will be expanded to spaces.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} autosave
If enabled, files will be automatically written when leaving a modified buffer.
@end defvr

@heading Search

@defvr {Setting} ignore_case Match case-insensitively
If enabled, searches will be perfmored case-insensitively.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} smart_case
If enabled, it will override @code{ignore_case} when a pattern has upper case
characters.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} incremental_search Enable incremental search
If enabled @code{vim} will perform incremental searches, rather than waiting
for the user to finish typing an accepting the search string.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} highlight_matches
If enabled @code{vim} will highlight all matches in the current file.
@end defvr

@heading Folding

@defvr {Setting} foldenable Enable folding large code
If enabled @code{vim} will allow to temporarily collapse or expand blocks of
code.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} foldlevelstart Code level to start folding at
folds with a level higher than this number will be closed.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} foldnestmax Maximum nested foldings
Maximum fold depth for when @code{foldmethod} is @code{indent} or @code{syntax}.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} foldmethod By default fold based upon
The method used to determine whether to fold large code blocks.
@end defvr

@heading Misc.

@defvr {Setting} show_lineno Display line numbers
Display line numbers.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} chdir Go into file's directory
Go into file's directory.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} highlight_line Highlight current line
Highlight current line.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} wildmenu Display possible completions
Display possible completion.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} highlight_column Highlight current column
Highlight current column.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} ruler Display the ruler
Display a customizeable ruler at the bottom.
@end defvr

@defvr {Setting} rulerformat rulerformat
Customize @code{vim}'s ruler.
@end defvr